==== Articles ====

# [[1969]] : Crisis: Volumes 22 à 23.- William Edward Burghardt Du Bois. ''National Association for the Advancement of Colored People''<ref>[http://books.google.fr/books?id=fb8WAQAAIAAJ&q=Saint-George&dq=Saint-George&hl=fr&ei=WoRxTNbVDo-u4QaK3Oj8Cg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=7&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBjjSAQ Saint-George] was the son of a black woman and of a Frenchman, a comptroller-general, M. de Boulogne, who called his mulatto son Saint- George after the stateliest vessel in the harbor of Guadeloupe.</ref>
# [[1976]] : {{Lien web |url=http://www.jstor.org/pss/1214399| titre=The Chevalier de Saint-Georges| auteur =Dominique-René de Lerma| année=[[1976]]| éditeur=Foundation for Research dans the Afro-American Creative Arts|site=jstor.org| consulté le = 18 mars 2001}}
